# ============================================
# .docker-env-chain — the project-level env chain (Layer 1).
#
# The compose-envkit shim (./docker, via scripts/compose-env.sh) reads this
# file, substitutes ${ENV} (a.k.a. ${COMPOSE_ENV}; resolved as shell COMPOSE_ENV
# > .env COMPOSE_ENV > "dev") and ${HOST} / ${HOSTNAME} (the machine hostname;
# override by exporting HOSTNAME), drops non-existent files, and feeds the result
# into COMPOSE_ENV_FILES. Each LATER layer OVERRIDES earlier ones (compose
# merges last-wins). Non-existent files are silently skipped.
#
# Container env_file: paths (the ones listed under each service in your
# docker-compose*.yml, e.g. db/.env.db, app/.env.app) are AUTO-DISCOVERED by
# scripts/parse-compose-env-files.sh — do NOT duplicate them here.
#
# Layout (committed templates → gitignored runtime copies):
#   Layer 1: root base + env-specific overlay
#     .env            ← non-secret defaults (cp from example.env)
#     .${ENV}.env     ← per-environment overlay (.dev.env / .prod.env / …)
#   Layer 2: SECRETS (last wins, gitignored)
#     .secrets.env    ← cp from example.secrets.env, fill real values
# ============================================

# Layer 1: root base + env-specific overlay
.env
.${ENV}.env

# Per-machine override (optional): selected by the hostname. Beats the shared
# .env / .${ENV}.env (per-dev tweaks: log level, local paths) but stays BELOW
# secrets. NEVER put secrets here. Uncomment to use; missing file ⇒ skipped.
#.${HOSTNAME}.env

# Layer 2: SECRETS (gitignored, override everything above) — MUST be last
.secrets.env
